  "text": "We love: fashion fixes for the week ahead – in pictures Hold your horsesBoho is back with a bang and where better to shop the trend than the original high-street home of the look: Monsoon. We love this embroidered denim dress styled with suede boots. £85, monsoon.co.uk Step aboardEssentiel Antwerp has teamed up with Sebago to create a fun spin on the classic boat shoe; available in two colour combinations with cherry and heart charms on the laces. Style with the matching argyle socks for some serious dopamine dressing action. Socks, £45 and shoes, £215, essentiel-antwerp.com Break a sweatMovement is at the heart of Saul Nash’s designs, making his SLNSH collaboration with Lululemon a natural fit. Spanning men’s and womenswear key pieces include a jacquard version of his signature compression top and a quarter-zip sweatshirt.From £48, lululemon.co.uk Wrap upOn those days when you can feel that spring hasn’t quite sprung, wrap up in this cheery red scarf. Plus 15% of profits from purchases go directly to the Mirasol school project in the Andean region of Puno where La Granni sources its alpaca yarn. £150, lagranni.com Island timeCarhartt WIP’s summer collection channels the relaxed spirit of Jamaica where the campaign was shot. Think relaxed fits, dropped shoulders and loose silhouettes across men’s and womenswear. Top, £100, carhartt-wip.com Sole mates FitFlop’s latest collaboration with designer Roksanda Ilinčić is inspired by Roksanda’s SS25 runway collection. Styles include a round-toe clog in shearling, cut-out sandals and platform heels with eye-catching shearling footbeds and ankle straps. From £160, fitflop.com Topics Fashion Men's fashion Men's tops Women's shoes Men's sportswear Women's sportswear",
